<title>Converter</title>
<p>This page explains all options for configuring the Converter in Preferences in <app>Tube Converter</app>.</p>

<terms>
	<item>
		<title>Disallow Conversions</title>
		<p>If enabled, Tube Converter will download the appropriate video/audio format for the selected quality without converting to other formats.</p>
        <p>This means that you will be unable to select a file format when downloading a media. But, you will save time in downloading as the Converter will not be run.</p>
		<note style="advanced">
			<p>Default: Off</p>
		</note>
    </item>
	<item>
		<title>Embed Metadata</title>
		<p>If enabled, Tube Converter will tag a media with its relevant information (title, genre, etc...) and thumbnail if available.</p>
        <p>Tube Converter will NOT embed the Comment, Description, Synopsis, and Purl fields.</p>
		<note style="advanced">
			<p>Default: On</p>
		</note>
    </item>
    <item>
		<title>Crop Audio Thumbnails</title>
		<p>Only available if Embed Metadata is enabled.</p>
		<p>If enabled, Tube Converter will automatically turn on the advanced option <code>Crop Thumbnail</code> for audio downloads.</p>
		<note style="advanced">
			<p>Default: Off</p>
		</note>
    </item>
	<item>
		<title>Embed Chapters</title>
		<p>If enabled, Tube Converter will tag a media with chapter information if available</p>
		<note style="advanced">
			<p>Default: Off</p>
		</note>
	</item>
</terms>
